# System Patterns — Burooj Corporate Website

## Architectural Overview
- **Nuxt 3** app using file-based routing for five core pages.
- **Layout-first approach:** `layouts/default.vue` wraps all pages with shared header/footer.
- **Composable-driven utilities:** `useGsap`, `useNavigation`, `useForm` to keep logic centralized.
- **Component library:** Base primitives (buttons, section wrappers) feed higher-level presentation components (stats, services, projects, contact form).
- **Data-as-config:** Static content stored in local arrays/constants for SSG until CMS integration.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Layout["layouts/default.vue<br>Header + Footer"] --> Pages["pages/*.vue<br>Home/About/Services/Projects/Contact"]
    Pages --> Components["components/*<br>(BaseButton, StatsGrid, etc.)"]
    Components --> Composables["composables/*<br>(useGsap, useForm, useNavigation)"]
    Composables --> Plugins["plugins/gsap.client.ts"]
```

**Diagram Description:** The layout wraps every page, which consumes reusable components. Components rely on composables for logic (animations, form state), while composables tap into client-only plugins such as GSAP registration.

## Design & Interaction Patterns
- **Hero + CTA pattern:** H1, supporting text, dual buttons (primary scroll, secondary external).
- **Section wrapper pattern:** Consistent `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16` container.
- **Card grid pattern:** Shared Tailwind classes for stats, services, projects, and clients with hover/focus states.
- **CTA blocks:** Gradient backgrounds, centered text, single primary button.
- **Animation hooks:** Use `ref`s + `useGsap` to register ScrollTrigger once per component; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Navigation & Layout Behavior
- **Sticky header** with transparent-to-solid scroll option (future enhancement).
- **Mobile drawer** toggled via `aria-expanded` attributes, closed on route change.
- **Footer grid** collapses to single column on mobile.

## Content Strategy Patterns
- **Service grouping:** Always display Construction & Engineering first, Property Management second, Drone (Burooj Air) teaser third with external CTA.
- **Projects:** Use consistent data shape `{ title, category, description, image }`.
- **Stats:** Provide numeric string plus label (and optional suffix) for counter animations.

## Animation Patterns
- Hero load-in sequence defined once and reused via `useGsap`.
- Section fade/slide triggered when 20‑30% of element is visible.
- Counters animate from 0 with `snap` to integers; run once per session.

